    "description": "Manufactured OpenAPI artifact for Mambu API Reference. This file was synthesized by Last Mile from curated research JSON and is not vendor-certified. Use it as an agent-consumable starting point, then validate paths, schemas, authentication, and server URLs with the vendor before production use. Mambu's public developer docs describe API v2 as the main RESTful surface for core banking features such as client and account management, transactions, general ledger journal entries, tasks, and system configuration, while also documenting API v1, Payments API, and Streaming API families. The public user guide states that Mambu APIs support creating clients, loan accounts, and savings accounts, making transactions, managing system configuration, setting up branches, configuring interest rates, and managing API keys, user roles, and access permissions. Mambu also states that OpenAPI specifications can be downloaded for all endpoints. This is a write-capable financial platform, but it does not represent asset or telemetry data. Asset data is Unsupported. Telemetry data is Unsupported. Writeback is Supported.",
